Known a-priori risks tracked during this project (see `configs/run_matrix.yaml` `known_risk` fields and `spike_tests/`):
- Mixtral-8x7B (MoE) + bitsandbytes support in vLLM is newer/less mature than dense-model bnb support.
- `bnb_4bit_use_double_quant` propagation through vLLM's `LLM()` API was verified via `spike_tests/spike_test_bnb_quant_args.py` before trusting the double-quant rows above.
- gemma-4-31B + bitsandbytes was verified via `spike_tests/spike_test_gemma4_bnb.py` (officially documented vLLM quantization paths for this model are W4A16/int8-per-channel, not bnb).

